# Phase 01: Add Edit Click to Worklog Activity

## Context Links
- Target file: `apps/web/ce/components/issues/worklog/activity/root.tsx`
- Modal: `apps/web/ce/components/issues/worklog/worklog-modal.tsx`
- Create button pattern: `apps/web/ce/components/issues/worklog/activity/worklog-create-button.tsx`
- Worklog types: `packages/types/src/worklog.ts`

## Overview
- **Priority**: P2
- **Status**: Complete
- **Description**: Add onClick handler + WorklogModal to IssueActivityWorklog component so users can click to edit their worklogs

## Key Insights
- `WorklogModal` already accepts `existingWorklog?: IWorkLog` prop for edit mode
- `worklog-create-button.tsx` shows exact pattern: `useState(false)` + render `<WorklogModal>` in fragment
- `useUserPermissions()` returns `{ allowPermissions }` function
- Backend should enforce: only ADMIN can PATCH/DELETE

## Permission Rules
- **Log time (create)**: Project member + Project admin
- **Edit/Delete**: Only **Project admin**

## Requirements
- Clicking a worklog activity entry opens WorklogModal in edit mode
- Only clickable if current user is **Project admin**
- Visual hint: Pencil icon on hover when user is admin
- cursor-pointer styling when user is admin

## Related Code Files
- **Modify**: `apps/web/ce/components/issues/worklog/activity/root.tsx`
- No new files needed

## Embedded Rules
- `observer()` on all MobX-reading components (already present)
- Use `@plane/propel/*` for UI components
- Semantic color tokens only
- Keep file under 200 lines
- Conventional imports: hooks from `@/hooks/store/...`, types from `@plane/types`

## Implementation Steps

<!-- Updated: Validation Session 1 - Added pre-steps for pattern grep and backend verification -->

### 0a. Grep existing edit-on-click patterns
Search codebase for existing patterns where activity/list items open edit modals on click. Match the UX convention (entire row vs icon-only, hover styles, cursor behavior) to ensure consistency.

### 0b. Verify backend permissions
Check worklog PATCH/DELETE view's `permission_classes` to confirm admin-only enforcement. If missing, add backend permission fix to this phase.

### 1. Add imports
```tsx
import { useState } from "react";
import { Pencil } from "lucide-react";  // add alongside existing Timer
import { EUserPermissions, EUserPermissionsLevel } from "@plane/constants";
import { useUserPermissions } from "@/hooks/store/user/user-permissions";
import { WorklogModal } from "../worklog-modal";
```

### 2. Add state and permission logic inside component
```tsx
const { allowPermissions } = useUserPermissions();
const [isEditModalOpen, setIsEditModalOpen] = useState(false);

// Only project admin can edit/delete worklogs
const canEdit = !!(worklog && allowPermissions(
  [EUserPermissions.ADMIN],
  EUserPermissionsLevel.PROJECT,
  workspaceSlug,
  projectId
));
```

### 3. Add click handler to outer div
- When `canEdit` is true: add `onClick={() => setIsEditModalOpen(true)}`, `cursor-pointer`, `hover:bg-layer-3`, `rounded-md`, `transition-colors`
- Keep `role="button"` and `tabIndex={0}` for a11y when editable
- Add `onKeyDown` for Enter/Space to open modal

### 4. Add Pencil icon (hover-visible)
Inside the `<p>` tag, after the date span:
```tsx
{canEdit && (
  <Pencil className="inline-block ml-1 h-3 w-3 text-color-tertiary opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity" />
)}
```
Add `group` class to the outer div.

### 5. Render WorklogModal
After the main div, inside a fragment wrapper:
```tsx
{canEdit && (
  <WorklogModal
    isOpen={isEditModalOpen}
    onClose={() => setIsEditModalOpen(false)}
    workspaceSlug={workspaceSlug}
    projectId={projectId}
    issueId={issueId}
    existingWorklog={worklog}
  />
)}
```

### 6. Wrap return in fragment
Current return is a single `<div>`. Wrap in `<>...</>` to include the modal.

