## Success Criteria
- Clicking worklog activity entry opens edit modal (for project admins only)
- Non-admin users see no visual change, no click handler
- Edit saves correctly via existing WorklogModal + store flow
- No regression on worklog display or create flow

## Risk Assessment
- **Low risk**: Single file change, reusing existing modal/store/API
- **Edge case**: `worklog` could be undefined if store hasn't loaded yet -> guarded by `canEdit` check requiring `worklog` to be truthy

## Security Considerations
- Frontend permission check: only Project ADMIN can edit/delete
- Backend PATCH/DELETE endpoints should also enforce admin-only permission
- Frontend check is UX-only (hides button), not security boundary
